\rem /s1 The Lord's Command to Rebuild the Temple; A Call to Rebuild the Temple; Zerubbabel restorer of the temple; A Call to Build the House of the Lord; The Command to Rebuild the Temple
\p
\v 1 In Dareyavesh's \add (Darius'sВҰ375563)\add* second yearВҰ375561 as kingВҰ375564 \add of Persia\add*, onВҰ375565 the 1st of the sixthВҰ375566 month, the prophetВҰ375577 HaggaiВҰ375576 brought Yahweh's messageВҰ375571 to the governorВҰ375584 of YehudahВҰ375585, ZerubavelВҰ375580 (Shealtiyel'sВҰ375583 son), and to the highВҰ375593 priestВҰ375592, Yehoshua (Yehotsadak'sВҰ375591 son), telling \add them that\add*\x + \xo 1:1: \xt Ezr 4:24вҖ“5:2; 6:14.\x*
\v 2 armyВҰ375599 commanderВҰ375599 Yahweh says, вҖңThese peopleВҰ375601 say that \add вүҲit's not the right\add* time to rebuildВҰ375612 Yahweh's \add вүҲresidence\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 3 Then YahwehВҰ375618 \add вүҲgave this messageВҰ375616\add* to the prophetВҰ375622 HaggaiВҰ375621 \add to tell the people\add*:
\m
\v 4 Is it a time for all of you to live in your panelledВҰ375630 housesВҰ375629, while \add вүҲYahweh's temple lies in ruins\add*?
\v 5 \add вүҲSoВҰ375635\add* now armyВҰ375639 commanderВҰ375639 YahwehВҰ375638 saysВҰ375637: вҖң\add вүҲDecide what you're all going to do\add*.
\v 6 You've all planted a lot, \add вүҲbut only harvestedВҰ375648 a littleВҰ375649. You've eatenВҰ375650, but it never fills you. You all drink, but never enough to satisfyВҰ375653 you. You put on clothes, but never feel warm enough. You earn wagesВҰ375664, but your pockets seem to be full of holes\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 7 \add вүҲSo\add* armyВҰ375674 commanderВҰ375674 YahwehВҰ375673 saysВҰ375672 \add again\add*: вҖң\add вүҲDecide what you're all going to do\add*.
\v 8 Go up into the hillsВҰ375682 and bringВҰ375683 back timber to buildВҰ375685 the \add вүҲtemple\add*. This will pleaseВҰ375687 and honour me,вҖқ saysВҰ375692 YahwehВҰ375693.
\p
\v 9 вҖңYou \add вүҲexpected\add* much, butВҰ375699 \add gained\add* littleВҰ375700. Anything you broughtВҰ375701 homeВҰ375702, I blew away \add again\add*. Why? ArmyВҰ375709 commanderВҰ375709 YahwehВҰ375708 says it's because my residence is still in ruins, while you're all \add busy\add* \add вүҲworking on\add* your own houses.
\v 10 That's why the sky withholds the dew andВҰ375731 the soil withholds itsВҰ375733 crops.
\v 11 I've \add вүҲsummoned\add* a droughtВҰ375736 onto the land and into the hillsВҰ375742, onto the grainВҰ375745 and the new wine, onto the oil and crops from the ground, onto \add both\add* people and livestock, and onto \add вүҲeverything you all do\add*.вҖқ
